7. MICRO-INTERACTIONS & MOTION

Motion should feel smooth and purposeful.

Use animations for:
‚Ä¢ focus session start
‚Ä¢ streak achievement
‚Ä¢ leaderboard movement
‚Ä¢ progress increases

Duration:
200‚Äì350ms

Use spring easing for natural feel.

Avoid flashy animations.

‚∏ª

8. PROGRESS & MOTIVATION VISUALS

Progress Charts

Strava-style progress graphs:
	‚Ä¢	simple lines
	‚Ä¢	soft glow highlight
	‚Ä¢	weekly trend clarity

Streak Visualization

Use:
üî• flame icon
or glowing streak counter

Focus Score Animation

Count-up animation increases engagement.

‚∏ª

9. FOCUS MODE UI

When focus session starts:

‚Ä¢ darken background slightly
‚Ä¢ reduce visual distractions
‚Ä¢ show minimal timer & task
‚Ä¢ calming gradient glow

UI should feel like entering a ‚Äúquiet zone‚Äù.

‚∏ª

10. INTERVENTION DESIGN

Prompts should feel helpful, not aggressive.

Use:
soft overlays
blur background
gentle motion

Avoid:
harsh popups
bright flashing alerts

‚∏ª

11. ICONOGRAPHY

Use clean outline icons.

Recommended libraries:
Feather Icons
Material Symbols
Lucide

Keep stroke consistent.

‚∏ª

12. ACCESSIBILITY

Minimum contrast ratio: 4.5:1
Text must be readable outdoors.
Tap targets ‚â• 44px.

‚∏ª

13. PERFORMANCE DESIGN

Avoid heavy gradients and large shadows on lists.
Use lightweight blur and optimize images.

Smoothness is more important than visual complexity.

‚∏ª

14. MOOD & EMOTIONAL FEEL

The app should feel:

calm
motivating
modern
smart
non-judgmental

Users should feel guided, not controlled.

‚∏ª

15. DESIGN CHECKLIST

Before finalizing a screen:

‚úî Is the most important info immediately visible?
‚úî Is there enough breathing space?
‚úî Does the interface feel calm?
‚úî Are progress elements motivating?
‚úî Is the screen understandable in < 2 seconds?

‚∏ª

DESIGN GOAL

Create an interface that makes focus feel natural, progress visible, and discipline rewarding.